gicon|ENG}} [[George Andrews (footballer)|George Andrews]] ('''51''') {{nowrap|<small>1972\u201377</small>}}\n* {{flagicon|ENG}} Johnny Devlin ('''51''') {{nowrap|<small>1947\u201352</small>}}\n* {{flagicon|ENG}} W. Robinson ('''51''') {{nowrap|<small>1907\u201309, 1910\u201313</small>}}\n* {{flagicon|NIR}} [[Kevin Wilson (footballer, born 1961)|Kevin Wilson]] ('''50''') {{nowrap|<small>1994\u201397</small>}}\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Notable Managers===\n{{Main|List of Walsall F.C. managers}}\nThe following managers have all made notable achievements for Walsall. Each has led the club to at least one of the following while in charge: winning promotion, reaching the final of a cup competition or recording the club's best result in a league season or cup competition.<ref name=\"WFCManagersSoccerbase\">{{cite web|url=https://www.soccerbase.com/teams/team.sd?team_id=2737&teamTabs=managers|title=Walsall Managers|work=Soccerbase|accessdate=14 July 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"HistoryBook\"/>{{rp|74\u201387}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!Name\n!Years\n!width=\"24\"|P\n!width=\"24\"|W\n!width=\"24\"|D\n!width=\"24\"|L\n!width=\"44\"|Win%\n!class=\"unsortable\"|Honours\n!class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|England}} G. Hughes <sup>sec</sup>\n|{{nowrap|1898\u201399}}\n{{WDL|35|15|12|8}}\n|align=left|<small>[[Football League Second Division|Second Division]] 6th place [[1898\u201399 in English football|1898\u201399]]</small>\n|align=left|{{efn|G. Hughes served as secretary-manager.}}\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[Andrew Wilson (footballer born 1896)|Andrew Wilson]]\n|{{nowrap|1934\u201337}}\n{{WDL|130|47|30|53}}\n|align=left|<small>[[Football League Third Division North Cup|Third Division North Cup]] runners-up [[1934\u201335 in English football|1935]]</small>\n|align=left|\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|England}} [[Tommy Lowes]]\n|{{nowrap|1937\u201339}}\n{{WDL|102|32|21|49}}\n|align=left|<small>[[FA Cup]] fifth rou