all League Second Division|Second Division]] 6th place [[1898\u201399 in English football|1898\u201399]]</small>\n|align=left|{{efn|G. Hughes served as secretary-manager.}}\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[Andrew Wilson (footballer born 1896)|Andrew Wilson]]\n|{{nowrap|1934\u201337}}\n{{WDL|130|47|30|53}}\n|align=left|<small>[[Football League Third Division North Cup|Third Division North Cup]] runners-up [[1934\u201335 in English football|1935]]</small>\n|align=left|\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|England}} [[Tommy Lowes]]\n|{{nowrap|1937\u201339}}\n{{WDL|102|32|21|49}}\n|align=left|<small>[[FA Cup]] fifth round [[1938\u201339 FA Cup|1938\u201339]]</small>\n|align=left|\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|England}} [[Harry Hibbs (footballer)|Harry Hibbs]]\n|{{nowrap|1944\u201351}}\n{{WDL|305|113|73|119}}\n|align=left|<small>[[Football League Third Division South Cup|Third Division South Cup]] runners-up [[1945\u201346 in English football|1946]]</small>\n|align=left|\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|England}} [[Bill Moore (footballer)|Bill Moore]]\n|{{nowrap|1957\u201363}}<br/>1969\u201372\n{{WDL|470|190|113|167}}\n|align=left|<small>[[Football League Fourth Division|Fourth Division]] champions [[1959\u201360 in English football|1959\u201360]]<br />[[Football League Third Division|Third Division]] runners-up [[1960\u201361 in English football|1960\u201361]]</small>\n|align=left|\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[Doug Fraser (footballer born 1941)|Doug Fraser]]\n|{{nowrap|1974\u201377}}\n{{WDL|163|60|45|58}}\n|align=left|<small>[[FA Cup]] fifth round [[1974\u201375 FA Cup|1974\u201375]]</small>\n|align=left|\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Scotland}} [[Dave Mackay (footballer born 1934)|Dave Mackay]]\n|{{nowrap|1977\u201378}}\n{{WDL|72|30|27|15}}\n|align=left|<small>[[FA Cup]] fifth round [[1977\u201378 FA Cup|1977\u201378]]</small>\n|align=left|\n|-\n|align=left|{{flagicon|England}} [[Alan Buckley]]\n|{{nowrap|1979\u201382}}<br/>1982\u201386\n{{WDL|349|148|92|109}}\n|alig