]]\n[[Category:Algerian drama films]]\n{{2010s-France-film-stub}}\n{{Algeria-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2015 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Let Them Come\n| image          = Let Them Come poster.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Salem Brahimi]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = Salem Brahimi\n| starring       = [[Rachida Brakni]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|2015|9|10|[[2015 Toronto International Film Festival|TIFF]]|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 95 minutes\n| country        = Algeria<br>France\n| language       = French<br>Arabic\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Let Them Come''''' ({{lang-fr|'''Maintenant ils peuvent venir'''}}) is a 2015 French-Algerian [[drama film]] directed by [[Salem Brahimi]].<ref name=\"yahoo\">{{cite web |url=https://fr.news.yahoo.com/blogs/ravanello/maintenant-les-distributeurs-peuvent-venir-153757115.html |title=Maintenant, les distributeurs peuvent venir |accessdate=28 August 2015 |work=Yahoo}}</ref> It was screened in the Contemporary World Cinema section of the [[2015 Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"variety\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/sandra-bullocks-our-brand-tom-hiddlestons-i-saw-the-light-to-premiere-at-toronto-1201572271/ |title=Sandra Bullock\u2019s \u2018Our Brand Is Crisis,\u2019 Robert Redford\u2019s \u2018Truth\u2019 to Premiere at Toronto |accessdate=23 August 2015 |work=Variety}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Rachida Brakni]] as Yasmina\n* [[Amazigh Kateb]] as Nouredine\n* [[Farida Saboundji]] as The Mother\n* [[Rayhana Obermeyer]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|4520338|Let Them Come}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Let Them Come}}\n[[Category:2015 films]]\n[[Category:2010s drama films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:French drama films]]\n[[Category:Algerian films]]\n[[Ca